AB  - We start from the fact that each spatial object i is characterized by three coordinates: x(latitude), y(longitude) and z i (by tradition elevation). The discussion proposed here turns around three axes : first, we remind some of the main problems when representing a volume (ellipsoid) on a plane (map). Second, we discuss some elementary principles of cartography in order to show the importance of the nature of z in thematic mapping. Third and last, we show how far the realistic representation of the third dimension can be improved by visualization techniques, a modern discipline close but different from cartography.
